Package de.yamass.redg.generator.extractor.nameprovider

Interface NameProvider

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultNameProvider, JpaMetamodelRedGProvider, JsonFileNameProvider, MultiProviderNameProvider
public interface NameProvider
This is the interface used for generating the class/method/variable names for the code generation. All methods in this interface must be deterministic. They are allowed to be stateful.

  • Method Details

    • getClassNameForTable

      String getClassNameForTable(schemacrawler.schema.Table table)
      Generates a class name for a database table. The returned string should adhere to the Google Java style Guide and consist solely of alphanumeric characters in UpperCamelCase. While numbers are discouraged, they may be used in the class name, though not at the start of the name.

      This method must be deterministic! Passing the same table multiple times has to yield the same result for each call.

      Parameters:
      table - The database table
      Returns:
      The generated name

    • getMethodNameForForeignKeyColumn

      String getMethodNameForForeignKeyColumn(schemacrawler.schema.ForeignKey foreignKey, schemacrawler.schema.Column primaryKeyColumn, schemacrawler.schema.Column foreignKeyColumn)
      Generates a method name for a database column that represents a foreign key or is part of a foreign key. E.g. the value of "OTHER_ID" column, not the method returning a RedGEntity. The returned string should adhere to the Google Java style Guide and consist solely of alphanumeric characters in lowerCamelCase. While numbers are discouraged, they may be used in the method name, though not at the start of the name.

      This method must be deterministic! Passing the same table multiple times has to yield the same result for each call.

      Parameters:
      foreignKey - The foreign key.
      primaryKeyColumn - The referenced database column.
      foreignKeyColumn - The referencing database column.
      Returns:
      The generated name
